Designing and Developing a RetrievalвЂ‘Augmented Generation (RAG) AI LLM

1. Introduction

RetrievalвЂ‘Augmented Generation (RAG) is an AI architecture that enhances Large Language Models (LLMs) by connecting them to external knowledge sources. Instead of relying only on preвЂ‘trained knowledge, RAG systems retrieve relevant documents from databases, vector stores, or APIs and use them to generate accurate, upвЂ‘toвЂ‘date responses.

RAG systems are increasingly used in:

* Enterprise AI assistants
* Customer support bots
* Knowledge base search engines
* Legal and medical research tools
* African infrastructure and development tools (aligned with EEWA concept)

This document provides a complete guide to designing and developing a RAG AI LLM.

